<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="92" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="92">
The older De Candolle name has been placed rather consistently in synonymy, but not adopted. It is only comparatively recently that the combination was occuppied in 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Vernonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. L. Nash" authorityYear="1974" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Compositae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vernonia tenella" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Vernonia tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
D.Nash, Fieldiana, Bot. 36: 74. 1974 = 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Rob" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="D. Nash" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lepidaploa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lepidaploa tenella" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">Lepidaploa tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(D.Nash) H. Rob. The epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Rob" authorityYear="1990" baseAuthorityName="D. Nash" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Lepidaploa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="tenella" order="Asterales" pageId="43" pageNumber="92" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="tenella">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="92">tenella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
still has priority in almost all other genera. The DeCandolle specimen is known in this study primarily from synonymy, description, and on the basis of microfiche (IDC DeCandolle Herbarium 197: III: 8).
</paragraph>
